The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Amway mulls new unit
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Amway mulls new unit
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Pinckney in Calcutta on Tuesday. Picture by Kishor Roy Chowdhury                                  
	Calcutta, June 22: Amway India  the countrys top direct selling FMCG company  is scouting for a location for a proposed facility that will double its capacity.         
	All Amway products are now sourced from seven third-party manufacturers across the country, the largest being at Baddi in Himachal Pradesh.        
	Amway India CEO William S. Pinckney said a decision on the new unit would be taken soon.         
	We are anticipating a strong growth. The present facility can hold out to a level of Rs 3,000 crore turnover factoring in present trend. But what if sales increase more than anticipated? he said.         
	The company expects a turnover of Rs 2,500 crore by 2012.        
	India is the only country where Amway has developed local products to cater to the specific needs of the customers. It contributes 30 per cent to total sales.                                                                                                                                       
